claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table comparing demographic and clinical characteristics (sex, race/ethnicity, coexisting illnesses, prior influenza vaccination) of participants receiving a recombinant vaccine versus a standard-dose vaccine, with counts and percentages for each group. does not support the claim because the table contains only participant demographics and clinical characteristics and provides no information on hemagglutinin (HA) microgram content per strain for Flublok or standard-dose vaccines
